// Signing & team configuration for Husky Notes.
//
// Husky Notes has NO server: every note lives on-device and (when sync is on) in
// each user's OWN private CloudKit database. The only account-specific value is
// the Apple Developer team you sign with — set it here, in ONE place, so the
// project builds under your account or a fork's without editing every target.
//
// IMPORTANT: this team MUST own the CloudKit container referenced in the
// entitlements (`iCloud.com.huskynotes.app`) and in PersistenceController, or
// iCloud sync will silently fall back to a local-only store.
//
// This is the team whose Apple Developer membership owns the app's identifiers,
// the iCloud container (`iCloud.com.huskynotes.app`) and the App Group
// (`group.com.huskynotes.app`) — CN-DESIGN LTD (Y769NRY4KQ). These identifiers
// are globally unique, so the project must sign under this team. To build under a
// fork's account, change this one line and register your own identifiers/container
// (see resources/CLOUDKIT_SETUP.md). Team IDs are not secret (they ship in apps).

DEVELOPMENT_TEAM = Y769NRY4KQ
